title: For Trade:  Ohio Buyers Beware
postcontent: Someone in Ohio (and possibly other states) is creating fraudulent listings using photos and descriptions from online gun auction sites like Gunbroker.  If you come across a listing that is "too good to be true", spend a few minutes first and check if that same item (using the same photographs) is for sale someplace else.  Just today, 3 rifles (including a Springfield M1A Bush rifle) were listed, received offers, and were closed down by the seller, but the actual Springfield rifle is still up for auction from a long-time seller in Tennessee.  Buyer beware!
